main event: An unidentified flying object was observed moving from south to north at Montauk AFS, New York.
interesting points: The object moved between 3300 RPM and descended 5000 ft.,The sighting lasted for about 10 to 15 minutes,The observer was a scope operator with unquestioned reliability,The object was noted to have moved against prevailing winds,The report indicates no identification of the object as known air traffic or weather balloons.
